hopobject.body: We went to university together defiance clinic pharmacy phone number As Borene noted, the key arguments for the increased use of drones by the military are that they don't put human pilots at risk and they have longer loiter times. Opposing arguments claim that they are too unreliable compared to human piloted aircraft and that they may be prone to errors. Other fears posit a day and age of artificial intelligence and self-guided automatons.
